---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="start here | human nature health"
  description="begin with the core principles of natural health and understand how the system works."
>
  <section class="page-hero section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow">start here</p>
      <h1>start with the few things that change the most.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        you do not need a perfect routine to feel better. you need a few powerful basics done
        consistently enough for the body to trust them.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <div class="content-block">
        <h2>1. improve sleep first (<a href="/how-to-fix-sleep">fix sleep</a>)</h2>
        <p>
          sleep changes almost everything. energy, mood, recovery, hormones, clarity, and stress
          tolerance all respond to better rest.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="content-block">
        <h2>2. get morning sunlight (<a href="/sunlight">learn more</a>)</h2>
        <p>
          one of the fastest ways to improve daily rhythm is to let natural light hit your eyes
          early in the day. it helps the whole system know what time it is.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="content-block">
        <h2>3. move every day (<a href="/movement">learn more</a>)</h2>
        <p>
          movement does not need to be intense to be powerful. walking, stretching, and strength
          work all help the body feel more alive and less stagnant.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="content-block">
        <h2>4. eat simpler, realer food</h2>
        <p>
          better health often begins when food becomes less chaotic. whole foods, stable meals,
          enough protein, and enough water go a long way.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="content-block">
        <h2>5. calm the nervous system (<a href="/nervous-system">learn more</a>)</h2>
        <p>
          overstimulation has become normal. slowing the system down through stillness, breath,
          lower input, and better rhythm can change how life feels from the inside.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="quote-block">
        <p>
          start with what is basic. the basics are often what people are missing most.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <div class="y2k-panel feature-card">
        <div class="panel-heading-row">
          <p class="panel-kicker">baseline</p>
          <span class="panel-stamp">start</span>
        </div>
        <h2>simple starting checklist</h2>
        <div class="content-list">
          <p><a href="/how-to-fix-sleep">fix sleep timing first</a></p>
          <p><a href="/sunlight">get sunlight early daily</a></p>
          <p><a href="/movement">walk or move every day</a></p>
          <p><a href="/food">eat simple, real meals</a></p>
          <p><a href="/nervous-system">reduce overstimulation at night</a></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>